<entry>
<author><name><![CDATA[tepples]]></name></author>
<updated>2006-10-09T08:19:43-07:00</updated>
<published>2006-10-09T08:19:43-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=2178&amp;p=18298#p18298</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=2178&amp;p=18298#p18298"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[CIC defeaters and Famiclones]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=2178&amp;p=18298#p18298"><![CDATA[
Most of the lockout defeaters just put -5 volts onto the CIC with a charge pump. Camerica carts had only one sequence, handled entirely by circuitry on the cart. But Nintendo locked out the Camerica carts by putting some passive elements around the CIC in later NES board revisions. Color Dreams carts adapted by using about nine different software-defined sequences to attempt to bypass the passive elements and freeze the CIC without overheating it, changing sequences after every reset.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Mon Oct 09, 2006 8:19 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
